From 6d598e0f8afd2f6bb38845d1fcf931822b0f12ff Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: reardonia <2925104+reardonia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 09:35:57 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 08/21] VAAPI: introduce CCapabilities for fourcc capability
 tracking

Replace CDecoder's static bool m_capGeneral / m_capDeepColor pair with a
CCapabilities object that tracks the set of VA fourccs the EGL interop
layer can import. Callers query CCapabilities::Supports(AVPixelFormat),
matching the ffmpeg-format vocabulary used elsewhere in the Kodi codec
and renderer code.

Single source of truth kVaFormatTable pairs each VA fourcc with its
VA_RT_FORMAT_* and matching ffmpeg AVPixelFormat. The probe layer
iterates the table; the caller queries it by AVPixelFormat. VA_FOURCC_*
constants stay encapsulated to the VAAPI module.

The OptionalsReg / WinSystem boundary keeps its existing general /
deepColor bool API. The GLES renderer's Register populates caps via a
new CVaapi2Texture::TestInteropFormats and derives the bool out-params
as views over the populated caps. CDecoder::Register no longer touches
m_capFormats - the renderer probe is the sole writer; the deepColor
parameter is preserved only for OptionalsReg signature compatibility.

No new fourccs probed in this commit; same NV12 / P010 set as before.
